The food was all really enjoyable.  Nothing was too dry; the food was met with good portion sizes; bbq sauce/meat ratio is well balanced.  The tables and chairs were clean, and the floors were acceptably clean.  The only reason I give it 4 stars instead of 5 is because due to how they plate their food.  They put the French fries under the meat instead of side by side, which in turn makes some of the otherwise nice-crisp/light crunch fries, a little bit soggy in parts that are underneath the meat.  Putting them side by side the meat would have prevented this. (Never underestimate the affects of how you plate foods together)  The cooking itself was perfectly executed. 👍👍👍👍👍
